args: Can I talk to you for a second,\n{player_name}?
It must be important if you came to my\nroom. What is it?
Look, I wanted to ask you for advice.
I want you to teach me what it means to be\na prince.
That is...not what I was expecting you\nto say.
Remember the song I sang for Lucretia?\nThe one that made her decide not to take\nme on tour with her?
That was a song about a prince who fights\nfor his kingdom.
I've been practicing it since I came here,\nbut it's just not working.
Really? Because I've heard you singing it,\nElias—it sounds pretty good to me.
Well, of course it would sound good to a\nlayman. But for a singer...
Well, this is hard to explain, but I don't\nthink I'm getting to the soul of the music.
And I think that's because I'm covering\na topic I know nothing about.
That may even be why Lucretia sent me\nhere in the first place.
You might have a point there.
Right? Anyway, that's why I wanted you\nto tell me your story.
I'm not acquainted with any other princes,\nyou know?
In that case, I'm happy to tell you my story.\nWhere should I begin...?
...So you left your castle in order to\nprotect your kingdom?!
I thought the only princes who did that\nkind of thing were the ones in faerie tales.
Heh. Well, I didn't exactly think I'd ever\nbe setting out to find Sacred Shards\nbefore I started this whole adventure.
So you weren't bothered by it?\nYou never wondered why this burden\nwas forced on your shoulders?
I mean, you could have DIED.\nWeren't you afraid?
Of course I was afraid. And I still am.\nBut I wasn't bothered.
I wanted so badly to bring peace to my\nkingdom, and that was stronger than\nany fear.
And even if this does end up killing me,\nthe Alberian royal family will continue so\nlong as our bloodline survives.
If I'm a stepping stone to that end,\nthat's enough.
But that would make everything you've\nsacrificed meaningless!

It's the duty of royalty to put the kingdom
first. Sometimes that means you sit on
the throne, and sometimes it means
you're the bricks in the floor.
That's...amazing. I could never do that.
I don't have the courage to risk my life\nfor a kingdom.
But you have your own kind of courage,\nElias. You know your weaknesses and\nyou're willing to face them.
That's nothing compared to what you've\ndone, {player_name}.
Which means no matter how long I spend\nwith you, I'll never understand what it\ntruly means to be a prince.
That's why Lucretia turned me down.\nBecause when I sing, it's with only a\nshallow, surface-level understanding.
Please don't try to console me—it's just\ngoing to make me even more depressed.
No, I'm seriously wondering if your singing\nis shallow or not.
I'm no musician, but I get that you're trying\nto know what it means to be a prince.
Which doesn't matter, because I'm failing.
But if you DIDN'T try to understand,\nthat would be even worse, right?
Right, but I sang just like the music told\nme to, which means this is... Wait.
I followed the music exactly, but...

Oh my gosh. When I first came here,
all I wanted to do was sing exactly as
the music said I should—but I STILL
wasn't understanding it!
Your singing has changed a lot since then.
I used to think I had to follow the score at\nthe expense of all else, but now I know\nthat's not really the case.
I also have to consider my fellow\nperformers as well as my audience.
I have to express what is BEHIND the lyrics\nof the song...which is a bit worrisome.
You've put significant thought and\neffort into your singing. I don't think\nit sounds shallow at all.
It's true that you're not a prince. But you\ncan still try to understand what it means\nto be one.
And the more experiences you have,\nthe easier that will become.
Do you see what I'm saying?
Honestly, I'm still young; I have a long\nway to go as a singer.
In that case, would you mind listening to\nmy song about the prince?
I'm going to think about you in my own\nway and put my thoughts into the song.
And don't be shy! Let me know if I'm not\nnailing that ＂princely＂ vibe.
